Wire the store to the existing watcher: when `state.json` transitions the bulk-YOLO's current issue from activeWork into history, write the next `/tiki:yolo {N}` command to the bulk-yolo terminal. On hard failure (issue marked failed in activeWork), call `recordFailure` and pause.

### Where to wire

The App.tsx `tiki-file-changed` listener (added in v0.6.2 #196) is the right place. It already detects `activeWork → history` transitions for the auto-refresh debouncer. Layer the bulk-YOLO advance check on top:

```ts
// In App.tsx, inside the stateChanged branch, after the existing
// detectGithubRefreshTriggers + scheduleRefresh calls:
if (prev && currentState) {
  // ... existing refresh detection ...

  const bulkRun = useBulkYoloStore.getState().runByProject[projectId] ?? null;
  if (bulkRun && bulkRun.status === 'running') {
    const currentIssue = bulkRun.queue[bulkRun.currentIndex];
    if (currentIssue !== undefined) {
      const wasActive = `issue:${currentIssue}` in (prev.activeWork ?? {});
      const nowDone = (currentState.history?.recentIssues ?? []).some((i) => i.number === currentIssue);
      const nowFailed = currentState.activeWork?.[`issue:${currentIssue}`]?.status === 'failed';

      if (wasActive && nowDone) {
        // Issue shipped — advance the queue and dispatch the next.
        useBulkYoloStore.getState().advance();
        dispatchNextBulkYolo();
      } else if (nowFailed) {
        useBulkYoloStore.getState().recordFailure(`Issue #${currentIssue} pipeline failed`);
        useToastStore.getState().addToast(
          `Bulk YOLO paused: issue #${currentIssue} failed. Fix and resume from the dialog.`,
          'error',
        );
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Helper: `dispatchNextBulkYolo`

New file: `apps/desktop/src/utils/bulkYoloDispatch.ts`. Pure logic + the side-effecting Tauri call.

```ts
import { invoke } from '@tauri-apps/api/core';
import { useBulkYoloStore } from '../stores/bulkYoloStore';

/**
 * Dispatch the bulk YOLO's next queued issue to its associated terminal.
 * Called after `advance()` or after `startRun + initial dispatch`. No-op if the
 * queue is exhausted or the run isn't in 'running' state.
 */
export async function dispatchNextBulkYolo(): Promise<void> {
  const store = useBulkYoloStore.getState();
  const run = store.runByProject[getProjectIdSafe()];
  if (!run || run.status !== 'running') return;
  const next = run.queue[run.currentIndex];
  if (next === undefined || !run.terminalId) return;

  try {
    await invoke('write_terminal', { id: run.terminalId, data: `/tiki:yolo ${next}\r` });
  } catch (err) {
    // Terminal may have been closed by the user. Pause and surface.
    store.recordFailure(`Failed to write to terminal ${run.terminalId}: ${String(err)}`);
  }
}

function getProjectIdSafe(): string {
  // Lazy require to avoid circular import at module load.
  const { useProjectsStore } = require('../stores/projectsStore');
  return useProjectsStore.getState().activeProjectId ?? 'default';
}
```

If the lazy `require` doesn't fly under tsc -b strict (it might not — ESM forbids), inline the projectId access into the call site or pass projectId as an arg:

