### Initial dispatch on startRun

When the dialog (Phase 3) calls `startRun`, it should immediately follow with `dispatchNextBulkYolo(projectId)` to fire the first command. The auto-advance handles all subsequent dispatches.

### Why one terminal

Using a single dedicated terminal (instead of N terminals) keeps the cascade observable in one place and avoids spawning a tab per issue. The user explicitly asked about this in the issue body — single dedicated terminal is the chosen answer.

### Edge cases

- **Watcher debounce vs cascade timing**: state.json gets multiple writes per issue (per-step transitions). We only advance on the activeWork→history transition, which only fires once per issue. Safe.
- **User runs another /tiki:yolo manually mid-cascade**: that issue moves through activeWork → history independently. Our `wasActive` check is keyed to the queue's current issue number, so manual runs don't trigger advance.
- **State write where the queue's current issue isn't even in prev.activeWork yet**: `wasActive` is false → no advance, no failure. Correct (probably the queued issue hasn't started yet, or was already completed before bulk YOLO started — unusual edge but harmless).

### Out of scope

- The dialog UI — Phase 3.
- The terminal-creation logic — Phase 3 (the dialog will do `addTabInBackground` and pass the new tabId in).
- Tests for the listener wiring — integration-shaped, deferred. Phase 3 will add a smoke test for the dispatch helper.

### Verification

- App.tsx's `tiki-file-changed` listener has a new branch that, when `useBulkYoloStore.getState().runByProject[projectId]?.status === 'running'`, checks for the current issue's activeWork→history transition (advance + dispatch next) or activeWork.failed transition (recordFailure + error toast).
- `apps/desktop/src/utils/bulkYoloDispatch.ts` exports `dispatchNextBulkYolo(projectId)` that writes `/tiki:yolo {N}\r` to the run's terminal via `invoke('write_terminal', { id, data })`. Failure path calls `recordFailure`.
- `pnpm build` clean. Test count unchanged this phase.

User-facing: a dialog that shows queue progress, current issue, completed list, failures. Pause/Resume/Abort buttons. Triggered from a 'Run YOLO' button in the BulkActionToolbar.

### New component: `apps/desktop/src/components/BulkYoloDialog.tsx`

Mounted globally at App root. Renders nothing when no run is active for the project. When active, shows a modal with:
- Header: 'Bulk YOLO — N of M complete' + status badge ('Running' / 'Paused' / 'Failed')
- Current issue: '#42 ⏳ executing' (read from tikiStateStore for the live status if available)
- Queue: ordered list of issue numbers + titles, each with status icon (✓ done, ▶ current, ⏸ pending, ✗ failed)
- Failures section (collapsed if empty): list of `{issueNumber, reason, at}` rows
- Buttons: Pause / Resume (toggle by status) / Abort (with confirm)
- Footer: 'Dispatching to terminal: <tabName>' (looked up via terminalStore.tabsByProject)

```tsx
import { useEffect } from 'react';
import { useBulkYoloStore, useProjectsStore, useIssuesStore, useTerminalStore } from '../stores';
import './BulkYoloDialog.css';

export function BulkYoloDialog() {
  const projectId = useProjectsStore((s) => s.activeProjectId) ?? 'default';
  const run = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.runByProject[projectId]);
  const pause = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.pause);
  const resume = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.resume);
  const abort = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.abort);
  const issues = useIssuesStore((s) => s.issues);
  const tabs = useTerminalStore((s) => s.tabsByProject[projectId] ?? []);

  if (!run || (!useBulkYoloStore.getState().isActive() && run.status === 'idle')) return null;

  const titleFor = (n: number) => issues.find((i) => i.number === n)?.title ?? `#${n}`;
  const tab = run.terminalId ? tabs.find((t) => t.activeTerminalId === run.terminalId) : null;

  const total = run.queue.length;
  const doneCount = run.completed.length;

  return (
    <div className="bulk-yolo-dialog" role="dialog" aria-label="Bulk YOLO progress">
      <div className="bulk-yolo-dialog__panel">
        <header className="bulk-yolo-dialog__header">
          <h3>Bulk YOLO</h3>
          <span className={`bulk-yolo-dialog__status bulk-yolo-dialog__status--${run.status}`}>
            {run.status}
          </span>
          <span className="bulk-yolo-dialog__progress">{doneCount} / {total} complete</span>
        </header>

        <ul className="bulk-yolo-dialog__queue">
          {run.queue.map((n, idx) => {
            const isCurrent = idx === run.currentIndex && run.status !== 'idle';
            const isDone = idx < run.currentIndex;
            const failed = run.failures.find((f) => f.issueNumber === n);
            const icon = failed ? '✗' : isDone ? '✓' : isCurrent ? '▶' : '○';
            return (
              <li key={n} className={`bulk-yolo-dialog__item bulk-yolo-dialog__item--${isCurrent ? 'current' : isDone ? 'done' : 'pending'}`}>
                <span className="bulk-yolo-dialog__icon">{icon}</span>
                <span className="bulk-yolo-dialog__num">#{n}</span>
                <span className="bulk-yolo-dialog__title">{titleFor(n)}</span>
              </li>
            );
          })}
        </ul>

        {run.failures.length > 0 && (
          <details className="bulk-yolo-dialog__failures" open>
            <summary>{run.failures.length} failure{run.failures.length === 1 ? '' : 's'}</summary>
            <ul>
              {run.failures.map((f, i) => (
                <li key={i}>#{f.issueNumber}: {f.reason}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </details>
        )}

        <footer className="bulk-yolo-dialog__footer">
          <span className="bulk-yolo-dialog__terminal">
            Dispatching to: {tab ? tab.name : '(terminal closed)'}
          </span>
          <div className="bulk-yolo-dialog__actions">
            {run.status === 'running' && (
              <button type="button" onClick={pause}>Pause</button>
            )}
            {(run.status === 'paused' || run.status === 'failed') && (
              <button type="button" onClick={resume}>Resume</button>
            )}
            <button type="button" className="bulk-yolo-dialog__abort" onClick={() => {
              if (confirm('Abort the bulk YOLO cascade? Completed issues stay shipped; queued issues are dropped.')) abort();
            }}>
              Abort
            </button>
          </div>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

