### BulkActionToolbar.tsx — Run YOLO button

Add a button next to the existing Add label / Remove label / Add to release / Close. Click handler:

```ts
import { useBulkYoloStore, useTerminalStore } from '../stores';
import { dispatchNextBulkYolo } from '../utils/bulkYoloDispatch';

const startRun = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.startRun);
const bulkActive = useBulkYoloStore((s) => s.isActive());

const onRunYolo = () => {
  if (busy || bulkActive) return;
  // Create or reuse a dedicated bulk-yolo terminal tab.
  const newTabId = useTerminalStore.getState().addTabInBackground();
  // Wait for the terminal to spin up. addTabInBackground returns the tab id but
  // the terminal id isn't synchronously available. The simplest approach: store
  // the tab id and let dispatch resolve the terminal id from it lazily.
  // For now, the dispatch helper accepts the *terminal* id, so we need the active
  // terminal id of the new tab. The terminalStore exposes activeTerminalIdByTab
  // via the Tab structure — see useTerminalStore.tabsByProject[pid].activeTerminalId.
  // Simpler path: poll briefly until the tab has an activeTerminalId, then start.
  // BUT — to keep this MVP shippable, just skip starting if the terminal isn't
  // ready and surface a toast: 'Open a terminal first, then click Run YOLO.'
  const tabs = useTerminalStore.getState().tabsByProject[projectId] ?? [];
  const newTab = tabs.find((t) => t.id === newTabId);
  const terminalId = newTab?.activeTerminalId;
  if (!terminalId) {
    addToast('Could not create bulk YOLO terminal. Open a terminal manually and try again.', 'error');
    return;
  }
  startRun(selected, terminalId);
  dispatchNextBulkYolo(projectId);
  clear(); // clear the selection — the bulk YOLO has its own queue snapshot
};

// In JSX:
<button type="button" disabled={busy !== null || bulkActive} onClick={onRunYolo}>
  {bulkActive ? 'YOLO running' : 'Run YOLO'}
</button>
```

The terminal-readiness race is real. If it bites, the fallback is: require the user to have a terminal open already and use the active terminal:
```ts
const activeTabId = useTerminalStore.getState().activeTabByProject[projectId];
const tab = tabs.find((t) => t.id === activeTabId);
const terminalId = tab?.activeTerminalId;
if (!terminalId) { addToast("Open a terminal first.", 'error'); return; }
```

Use the active-terminal-required path to ship MVP. Document in the dialog footer that this terminal is the cascade target.

